<section aria-labelledby="faq-section" id="faq">  
  <div
    class="mx-auto w-full lg:px-24 max-w-7xl md:px-12 items-center px-8 py-24 scroll-mt-12"
  >
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 lg:gap-12">
      <div class="text-center lg:text-left">
        <div>
          <p
            class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-4xl"
          >
            Frequently asked questions
          </p>
          <p class="text-base mt-4 text-zinc-500">
            Answers to commonly asked questions about TabTab
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div
        x-data="{
  activeAccordion: '',
  setActiveAccordion(id) {
  this.activeAccordion = (this.activeAccordion == id) ? '' : id
  }
  }"
        class="relative w-full mx-auto font-normal lg:col-span-2"
      >
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-black"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>How does TabTab work?</span>
            <svg
              style="min-width: 20px; min-height: 20px; width: 20px; height: 20px;"
              class="duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500 flex-shrink-0 !shrink-0"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div x-show="activeAccordion==id" x-collapse="">
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              TabTab uses Apple's Accessibility framework to control your Mac
              and see details about which windows and tabs you're using. 
              <br>
              It is a fully native macOS app built with AppKit and SwiftUI.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>Is the app free to use?</span>
            <svg
              style="min-width: 20px; min-height: 20px; width: 20px; height: 20px;"
              class="duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500 flex-shrink-0 !shrink-0"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div x-show="activeAccordion==id" x-collapse="">
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Yes, you can download and use the app for free. However, to unlock unlimited tracking of windows and tabs, you can upgrade to the Pro tier.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span
              >Is a subscription required?</span
            >
            <svg
              style="min-width: 20px; min-height: 20px; width: 20px; height: 20px;"
              class="duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500 flex-shrink-0 !shrink-0"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              No. TabTab is a one-time purchase. There will be free future updates.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>What is the refund policy?</span>
            <svg
              style="min-width: 20px; min-height: 20px; width: 20px; height: 20px;"
              class="duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500 flex-shrink-0 !shrink-0"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div x-show="activeAccordion==id" x-collapse="">
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              We stand by our app with a 7-day money-back guarantee. If you’re not satisfied for any reason, do reach out at <strong><em>riccqi [at] pm [dot] me</em></strong> within 7 days of purchase and we’ll issue a full refund — no questions asked. 
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span
              >How is my data handled?</span
            >
            <svg
              style="min-width: 20px; min-height: 20px; width: 20px; height: 20px;"
              class="duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500 flex-shrink-0 !shrink-0"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Privacy is essential for an app that is part of your daily workflow. TabTab does not collect any user data. Everything is processed locally on your Mac and never sent out of your device.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
